but tbh in activisions defense, black ops 2 and 3 were two of there most popular games 
(literally BO2 was there most sold game ever)
THEN the community called COD the same every year in 2013. so im not surprised they chose COD in space as a thing because the community said they wanted different and they got it. not to mention theyre most sold game ever (according to CEO of activision) was BO2. SO they was just like "HEY WE SHOULD PROBABLY MAKE A NEW AND MORE INNOVATIVE COD GAME TO COME OUT THIS YEAR INSTEAD OF COD GHOST 2 PLUS THE COMMUNITY IS ASKING FOR SOMETHING DIFFERENT", and even thoe that was a horrible way to read the words of the community, they was only trying to listen to the fans

i mean honestly, its like we took the "worst case scenario" route to the COD series 

because if they would have never looked at the community's non sense and continued making games how they would have
this would be the COD order right now.

Call of duty: Modern Warfare 3
Call of duty: Black Ops 2
Call of duty: Ghost
Call of duty: Vietnam
Call of duty: WAW2/BO3 (unsure if activision "decided" black ops 3)
Call of duty: Ghost 2

^THAT ACTUALLY LOOKS LIKE A NORMAL COD ORDER but this is what we got

Call of duty: Modern Warfare 3
Call of duty: Black Ops 2
Call of duty: Ghost
Call of duty: Advanced Warfare
Call of duty: Black ops 3
Call of duty: Infinite Warfare
^
if there is a alternate universe where we got the other order, i bet if we showed them the line up now, the entire gaming community of that universe would be laughing theyre azzes off right now


(i also have proof of this stuff to, its all in activisions response to infinite warfares dislikes, and the top 10 cod games that never came out lol i forgot who made that video btw. also i found these out just by simply stumbling upon videos, if i actually did some research i would probably be able to confirm it in STEEL. but at the moment, this is enough evidence to confirm that we (the cod community) made these future cods when we cried about COD being the same game every year.

honestly its as simple as this.

you ask for something

you get something in return

if u dont like it, you should have never asked for it.

Comment: Infinity Ward, I think I speak for all of us when I say: We didn't want this kind of change. We didn't want exo jumps, futuristic eras, or even supply drops. It just needed more content. Look at CoD: Online. That game is a perfect example of what kind of change we needed. We want a CoD game that is in the modern era, but still has old, and new guns, melee weapons, game modes and maps. We also want a campaign that introduces new, and old characters, also adding a great storyline with action, and emotions. And last but not least, we want new extra modes. Not just survival, and zombies, but new modes like those crazy, and chaotic alien modes from CoD: Online. That is the kind of game we want next year. But that's just my opinion.

Title: Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare Reveal Stream
Comment:
Oh please don't completely follow in Treyarch's footsteps with map designs. Their maps have always been so lackluster.. Stick to the true IW map styles, which have always been about intricate layouts, providing dynamic manoeuvrability, amazing lines of sights and no unnecessary invisible walls on places where little toddlers could climb onto in real life, but in damn Lag Ops series, you have super soldiers who can't even get up on some of the ledges.

For me, every COD installment made by IW have had AMAZING maps. The whole hate on Ghosts' map sizes was just blown wayyyy out of proportion. Apart from Siege and Stonehaven, the other maps were really good sizes, and for some reason a lot of the COD community have memory loss towards anything that happened before BO2, because COD maps have always been that size on average.

So please stick to your classic, vintage, signature IW map styles. I'm SICK of all these BO2/3 maps with 3 lanes and a headglitch post at every corner or chokepoint, it's pathetic. It just encourages and rewards camping. In IW maps, the bad players can't thrive the way they do in Treyarch maps, and you have to follow a much more deeper learning curve to learn to adjust to the rhythm and flow of the maps. The good and bad players are all in their rightful places, unlike 3Arc Productions where they're just all over the place and the skill gap has been significantly reduced.

Oh and also, PLEASE KEEP RICOCHET IN HARDCORE PLAYLISTS! 
Thank you.

Forever an Infinity Ward fanboy <3

Title: Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare Reveal Stream
Comment: I remember back then I used to complain about ghosts and demanding changes to call od duty, but it seems like activision completely got the idea wrong. When I asked for changes, I meant smaller maps, newer perks and weapon attachments that would add new abilities to the multiplayer experience, more customization and a completely original and innovating campaign story set in the modern era (i'm pretty sure i'm not the only one asking for these changes). What do i get instead? Jetpacks, wallrunning, fictional weapons, useless scorestreaks (advanced warfare mostly), Space Combat and the thing that i completely despised the most: the complete shift into a far future beyong science fiction (what infinite warfare is turning out to be). I'm aware that black ops 2 began with the future bullcrap, but at least it had guns that do exist in our world such as the an 94, the scar h, the mtar and that was enough for me to keep playing the game.

Title: Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare Reveal Stream
Comment: The stories the games have are pretty interesting, but they just can't be told in 20 20 minute missions. Thats why the older games were better(that and the simple mechanics) there wasn't too much story, we already knew what was going on, at least in the world war 2 games. The modern warfare series was in a familiar time, so there was no need for over explanation as the player related to the environment. Now everything needs to be explained because none of the stuff in the games is relatable to the player. This works in Assassins Creed and Destiny because those are 20+ hour games with story and lore built into those hours, COD doesn't have missions long enough to fully flesh out these kinds of stories. The mechanics are also too much, sure they're cool, but they don't give us the feel the old(better) games did. The only things I can see being improvements as mechanics are sliding and being able to hurdle over small walls. But mech suits aren't needed nor are these special ability things we have now. Just because Destiny and Titan Fall were futuristic does not mean COD needs to be.... I could go on

For all the people mad about the 'futuristic' COD just know that the company didn't know the community hated this new style because Infinity Ward was already working on this game for at least a year possibly a year and a half before they found out. They obviously wouldn't start over again.

I honestly am really excited for the game, I get bored of COD so easily because its the same thing but if this changes up a lot that could make the game better. I can just imagine a gamemode where its 9v9 dogfights in spaceships. It wouldn't be mandatory to play but it would be fun.

So don't get mad at what the game looks like now, just wait, give it a go and have an open mind and you may find one of your favourite games ever.

Title: Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare Reveal Stream
Comment: Call of duty started in World War 2. People liked it at first, then complained they wanted a call of duty in modern times. So they gave us modern warfare. People liked that at first, then when they got bored of that, they complained they wanted a futuristic call of duty. At that moment, treyarch, sledgehammer, and infinity ward all started working on futuristic games. 3 years later advanced warfare comes out, and again, people like it at first, but when treyarch and infinity ward make a futuristic one, people complain that they want to go back to modern war/WW2. As soon as they do that, people will complain and eventually ask for futuristic warfare again. Seriously, the call of duty community is hard to please. You guys don’t know how good the game is until its gone. Years from now, when people are saying they want futuristic call of dutys again, they’ll look back and actual LIKE Advanced warfare and Black ops 3 and Infinite Warfare. They just can’t ever be please, and don’t know what the have until it’s gone. Im a HUGE fan of call of duty, and I personally LIKE Advanced warfare, and Black Ops 3 and I’m SUPER exited for Infinite Warfare. I mean, give infinity ward a chance. They had 3 years to make this game! It will probably be good! It isn’t even out yet, and you guys are complaining.
